    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1870-12-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1870-12-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="363" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d363">
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">No. 342.</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">General Sickles</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr. Fish</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1870-12-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">December</hi> 19.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Reply received to-night. Bases include numerous provisions. I send synopsis
                        of those inconsistent with your instructions.</p>
                <p>Both governments shall submit pending reclamations to arbitration in
                        conformity to following propositions:</p>
                <p>First. No indemnity for injuries resulting from judgment of civil or military
                        court or other judicial proceeding agreeably to Spanish law and
                        procedure.</p>
                <p>Second. It must appear that the Spanish authorities inflicting the injury
                        were informed of the nationality of the claimant.</p>
                <p>Third. No right to indemnity if claim to American citizenship has been
                        disallowed by judgment of any Spanish civil or military tribunal.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>SICKLES.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
